  "description": [
    "BIX EYEWITNESS TO RU M RUNNING GIVES INSIDE LONDONOne of the few gen uine eye witness stories of rum running from the inside has just been revealed here by Fred Harris a steward and cook who unwitting ly found himself signed up as steward on a rum runner His story came out not by way of a protest against bootlegging but as a protest against ship owners signing a crew without advising its members of the real nature of the voyage As a result of his experi ence he came back staggered by the immensity of the rum running or ganization and by the magnitude of its operations Signed Up in Ignorance I and 20 others were signed on a freighter bound from Newcastle onType for Antwerp and thence to Halifax said Harris in telling of his experiences So far as any of us knew it was simply a general cargo voyage The first intimation we had that the ship was a rum runner was when 35000 cases of whisky were taken aboard at Ant werp We arrived at ltum Row three weeks later Smaller boats came alongside and we were all ordered out to help handle the stuff The"
  ],
